    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## AI Fraud Detection\r\n\r\nExamine how well an AI system detects fraud compared to your own analysis.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\nLoad the same user artifacts that you looked at to AI and compare:\r\n1. Did the AI flag the same thing?\r\n2. Did it miss anything?\r\n3. Did it catch something a human wouldn't?\r\n\r\n\r\n**Try it out!** \r\n\r\n:::details [<i class=\"fa fa-briefcase\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Need a starting prompt?**]\r\n>Please review this user's background, login log, and transaction history. What behavior seems suspicious or possibly fraudulent, and why?\r\n:::\r\n&nbsp\r\n\r\n\r\n::: details [<i class=\"fa fa-file-image-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **How do I add a user profile and audit logs?**]\r\n- Click the button labeled **Add** below your chat input.\r\n- Choose **From Library**\r\n- Then browse the existing files.\r\n- When you find your user's file to upload, click the checkbox next to it to select it and then click **Attach**.\r\n- You should see the file get added to the message being sent to AI Chat.\r\n:::\r\n",
